  "market_context": "Bitcoin price had swept prior daily low, closed back inside range, forming a bearish change in state of delivery. Analyst used daily Next Day Model to anticipate downside, then dropped to hourly for entry.",
  "key_observation": "Daily candle closed back inside previous candle’s range with large lower wick, signaling bearish bias; hourly showed retest of order block followed by propulsion block formation for short entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On daily chart, observed price swept previous candle low and closed back inside the range, indicating bearish bias via Next Day Model.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to hourly timeframe to locate POIs: identified a bullish order block (OB) around 60400–61600 as a retest zone.",
    "Step 3: Watched for change in state of delivery: price reached the OB, formed a closure below the opposing candle series, confirming bearish CISD.",
    "Step 4: Identified a propulsion block forming off the OB after the closure, with opening price at ~61600 and mean threshold near 60400.",
    "Step 5: Entered short at close of propulsion block candle, stop placed above the high of that candle (~62800), targeting 2R toward prior lows (~59800)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade achieved 22R profit before lows were taken out; price continued lower after entry.",
  "lessons": "Next Day Model on daily provides directional bias; valid entries require confluence of HTF bias, LTF POI (OB), and CISD/propulsion block confirmation. Always wait for higher-time-frame closure before committing.",
